
[1]hegira

   HEGI'RA, n. In chronology, an epoch among the Mohammedans, from which
   they compute time. The event which gave rise to it was the flight of
   Mohammed from Mecca; from which the magistrates, fearing his impostures
   might raise a sedition, expelled him, July 10, A.D. 622,under the reign
   of the emperor Heraclius.
